[Visual Basic] ' Be sure to import the namespace by putting "Imports Dart.PowerTCP.SecureMail" ' at the top of your class.
' *** EndSend Event ***
' You can either use the AddHandler statement to associate an event with an event handler in your init code AddHandler Smtp1.EndSend, New Dart.PowerTCP.SendEventHandler(AddressOf Smtp1_EndPut)
' Or you can use the Handles keyword to associate an event handler with an event Private Sub Smtp1_EndSend(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As Dart.PowerTCP.SecureMail.SmtpEventArgs) Handles Smtp1.EndSend End Sub [C#] // Be sure to import the namespace by putting "using Dart.PowerTCP.SecureMail;" // at the top of your class.
// EndSend event this.smtp1.EndSend += new Dart.PowerTCP.SecureMail.SendEventHandler(this.smtp1_EndSend);

